did.unittitle: Materials Recorded at Copper Center, Alaska
did.abstract: Ahtna songs and stories recorded at Copper Center, Alaska in 1968 by Frederica de Laguna. Includes dance songs, sorry songs, potlatch songs, sleep doctor songs, and others. Includes "Gulkana Potlatch Given by Bill Joe and Kate Sanford for Recovery of Maggie Joe from Illness." Some songs are Tlingit, Upper Tanana, or Tanacross in origin. Also includes Ahtna stories, autobiographical accounts, vocabularies, and interviews.
did.physdesc: 27 sound tape reels (14 hr., 55 min.) : analog, 7 1/2 ips, 2 track, mono ; 5 in. and 7 in.

odd.head: Note on numbering
odd.p: Tapes are numbered 1-28, with no tape 18.

Given the location of the recording, a significant portion of the songs are likely in the Upper Tanana language.
